{
  "stem": "19895.7",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 371.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I wrote down names, but I don't know if you should list the names one by one here, whom I remember from the family who did not make it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and I have an uncle by the name of Laszlo Lichtmann, who my father's brother-- half brother because father's mother died in childbirth-- didn't make it from concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Father's sister, Margit, didn't make it-- died in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We don't know exactly who died where, which one.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Sometimes, some few survivors could be contacted, and they said that possible from that location.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Many of these relatives didn't live in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were less fortunate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The city of Budapest, even so if I was taken away, even so if my mother, which I didn't speak much about yet, because we didn't know what her fate was, was taken away.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the Budapest Jews were not so heavily victimized by the final solution of the Third Reich Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And talking about mother, one day, Father comes home and says, I can't tell you how much hope we have for mother being alive.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In that newspaper's fence where the list of people are put out, I read the name of Ida Schleyer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I read the birth place, which is [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I read the year of birth, which wasn't hers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a number of years younger than hers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But if she would have known another Ida Schleyer in [NON-ENGLISH], she would have talked about it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I think for whatever reason, either they misprinted it, but there is hope that it is she who-- whose name I found.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And according that list, the International Red Cross is publishing the list, she is in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So how to contact the International Red Cross in this war-torn country which starts to emerge.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
